comments: The first parts of the word were easy to latch onto, (zeti for star shape, buvy for pentagon, wopy for circle etc), it took a little bit longer for me to latch onto the secondary part coe or coh, but again it came with a logical pattern (coh was for grey buvy for instance), the majority seemed to be coe, so learning the exceptions that were coh seemed to be the best way around it. That said while I now feel like i can remember the first part of the words easily i cant recall the secondary rules so easily- so i probably just soaked those in more subconsciously and reacted/linked them to the visual stimulus.
